I don't think I've ever come across an SCP where the assumed reader is a civillian (closest I can recall is Jekeled's [sadly] self-deleted SCP wherein the file was captured documentation in the possession of Serpent's Hand members), so for that, this gets bonus points for having a decent level of originality.

While the basic idea is something I can totally get behind, the execution leaves much to be desired. It's all so very shallow - a brief overview of what the Foundation is, delivered through annoyingly short bursts - it's quite irritating to have the level of interaction limited essentially to nodding every couple of seconds.

I'd love to see another approach to this that goes a little more above and beyond in terms of substance. In its current state, there's nothing here to maintain intrigue. It feels like a waste of a good idea, having nothing to it in terms of actual content. -1







